article.headline: Sam Houston St. 92, Brown 79
article.story: COLUMBIA, Mo. (AP) -- Eddy Fobbs scored eight points in the first 2:03 of the second half to spark Sam Houston State to a 92-79 win in the consolation game of the Guardians Classic on Tuesday night. After committing two early fouls and spending most of the first half on the bench, Fobbs scored four of the first five baskets in the second half to give the Bearkats (1-1) a 50-42 lead. He committed two quick fouls a few minutes later and fouled out with 1:57 left, but his 11 points in 11 minutes were enough. Wilder Auguste had a similar run midway through the second half. He scored seven consecutive points for the Bearkats, extending their lead to double digits, and finished with 25 points. Brown (0-2) played without guard Jason Forte, last season's Ivy League player of the year, who coach Glen Miller suspended indefinitely for conduct detrimental to the team. That left the Bears with one starter from last season, Luke Ruscoe, whose 17 points on 6-of-7 shooting in the first half kept the Bears in the game. Ruscoe was quiet in the second half and finished with 25 points. Brown lost despite another hot night from the outside. After making 11-of-21 3-pointers in a 68-60 loss to Missouri on Monday, the Bears made 9-of-19 against Sam Houston State. After committing 29 turnovers in a first-round loss to Houston on Monday, the Bearkats committed just six on Tuesday.
